query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `building_sections` (
  `id` int NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `projectId` int NOT NULL,
  `name` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `description` text,
  `sectionType` enum('original','extension','addition','renovation') NOT NULL DEFAULT 'original',
  `installDate` date,
  `expectedLifespan` int,
  `grossFloorArea` decimal(10,2),
  `numberOfStories` int,
  `constructionType` varchar(100),
  `notes` text,
  `createdAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updatedAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `idx_project_id` (`projectId`)
)
